children.subject: I heard all the CSM 70 senior mentors and coordinators are extremely helpful, cool and simply put, great people to be around with! This sounds very exciting - I'll apply!
You've sure grabbed my attention. Count on my application!

history.content:
CSM is looking for mentors to teach CS 70 (discrete math and probability) this fall!

CSM mentors lead their students in small-group sections and individualized teaching settings, work with a family of like-minded mentors to improve their own teaching, and gain support from the larger community of students, teachers, and mentors in CSM.

The application is available at https://tinyurl.com/CSMfa20-apply and is due this Sunday 8/16. 

We’re a group of passionate students and mentors who are creating an open and inclusive community for computer science and electrical engineering students to receive individualized academic and social support, and we need your help to make that happen. We are currently recruiting mentors for CS 61A, CS 88, CS 61B, CS 61C, CS 70, EECS 16A and EECS 16B.

As is relevant to CSM 70, we hear your concerns about some of the recent changes to content and are working this semester to address them to make CSM more meaningful to both mentors and mentees.
